{"questionId":"3131406","questionHtml":"<p>For the optimal route, verify that the equation in part (c)(ii) satisfies the following result:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>speed</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>over</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>field</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>speed</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>over</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>rough</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>ground</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>.</mo></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><msqrt><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mfrac></math>&nbsp; <strong>AND</strong>&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><msqrt><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>64</mn><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A</strong><strong>1</strong></em></p>\n<p>substituting in the above equation and rearranging&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math> leading to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mn>15</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>verifying the result&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>x</mi><msqrt><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><msqrt><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>64</mn><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>attempt to rearrange into a quotient&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>15</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi>x</mi><msqrt><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mfrac></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><msqrt><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>64</mn><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mfrac></mstyle></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>verifying the result<strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"3131406","referenceCode":"23M.3.AHL.TZ2.1ciii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"For the optimal route, verify that the equation in part (c)(ii) satisfies the following result: cos HP^Mcos SP^N=speed over fieldspeed over rough ground.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.7—Optimisation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}